These is the readme file for the TI Category Picker extension.

== Download ==

Get the latest copy at https://github.com/nischayn22/TI-Category-Picker/archive/master.zip

== About ==

TI Category Picker is an extension to MediaWiki that lets users select a Category as a form input by drilling in the Category tree using dropdowns.

== Installation ==

To install you must have the following lines in your LocalSettings.php in the same order.

require_once( "$IP/extensions/DataValues/DataValues.php" );
require_once( "$IP/extensions/Validator/Validator.php" );
include_once("$IP/extensions/SemanticMediaWiki/SemanticMediaWiki.php");
enableSemantics('mysite');
require_once( "$IP/extensions/SemanticForms/SemanticForms.php" );

require_once("$IP/extensions/TICategoryPicker/TICategoryPicker.php");

== Usage ==

To use this extension you can use the form input name 'TI Category Input' like this

{{{field|category|top category=Products|input type=TI Category Picker}}}

Where top category implies the category to start building the Category Tree.